==English==
'''Dog Days'''
===Noun===
# The days between early July and early September when Sirus (the [[Dog Star]]) rises and sets with the [[Sun]].
# Hot, lazy, days.
# A period of inactivity, laziness or stagnation.

===Etymology===

Derived from the hot days (in the [[Northern Hemisphere]]) between early July and early September when Sirus (the [[Dog Star]]) rises and sets with the [[Sun]].  Due to the heat strenuous effort is typically kept to a minimum.

